  <title>Edit a file as the root user</title>

  <note style="warning">
    <p>Editing files as the root user is potentially dangerous, and may break
    your system in bad ways. Take great care when editing files as the root
    user.</p>
  </note>

  <p>To edit files as the root user, launch <app>bedit</app> from the terminal
  by entering:</p>
  <code>sudo bedit</code>

  <p>Using the <cmd>sudo</cmd> command, you will need to successfully enter
  your password before <app>bedit</app> will open.</p>

  <p>As an alternative to the <cmd>sudo</cmd> command, you may obtain
  administrative privileges by entering:</p>
  <code>su -</code>

  <p>You would then launch <app>bedit</app> using the <cmd>bedit</cmd>
  command.</p>

  <note style="tip">
    <p>Once you have opened <app>bedit</app> with administrative privileges,
    <app>bedit</app> will keep those privileges until you close it.</p>
  </note>

